#X text 55 -322 Used for fexpr~ only:;
#X text 55 -266 $y[n]: the output value indexed by n where n has to
satisfy 0 > n >= -vector size.;
#X text 55 -238 (the vector size can be changed by the "block~" object.)
;
#X text 55 -307 $x#[n]: the sample from inlet # indexed by n where
n has to satisfy 0 => n >= -vector size \, ($x# is a shorthand for
$x#[0] \, specifying the current sample);
#X text 140 -192 $y -> $y1[-1];
